Maybe this is worth keeping as a normal note
`ext` doesn't happen to have gotten smarter yet?

No. I think we long ago decided that the new `ext` behaviour is better. Library authors need to add additional `@[ext]` lemmas if there are situations where the new `ext` will not break open definitions that the old `ext` was willing to. (The old `ext` just blindly calls `apply` with every `ext` lemma. The new `ext` uses a discrimination tree.)
`linarith` seems pretty heavy for what it needs to do here. No objection if you prefer it, though
Switched to `omega`. I never do arithmetic by hand if I can help it, even if it's a single step. :-)
